Package: validatepop
Type: Package
Title: Perform Common Validations On Demographic Data
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Chris Fairless
Maintainer: Chris Fairless <christopher.fairless@london.gov.uk>
Description: Functions that perform common checks on demographic dataset,
    throwing errors when the inputs are not what is expected.
    Currently contains two functions, validate_population(), 
    which checks that a dataset conforms to a set of expectations about a population dataset,
    and validate_join_population() which checks that one population's aggregation levels
    are contained within another's and that a join will behave as expected.
License: GLA internal use
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Suggests: 
    testthat
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
Imports: 
    assertthat,
    dplyr,
    rlang
